caption: Definitely some of the best chicken I ever had. It had a good spicy kick to it. Fresh hot crispy chicken with a crackling sound when you bite and pull the flesh from the bones.

The best hot chicken in Chicago, IL,. We always get 2 sliders- hot flavor. We come here about every two weeks and it has never disappointed. We tried Howlin Rays out first and did not enjoy half as much as we like Dave's. Plus, the line at Dave's moves very quick!

Worth the hype!!! I love chicken and I love spice! I love spicy chicken!!! This place is top notch juicy crispy chicken with stages of spice for all levels. Fries are perfectly crispy and flavorful with that seasoning on top. The sauces are a must! Dip that spicy in the sweet honey to take your mouth to flavortown! Lol  Loved it! Definitely try this place out! No regrets!

Best times to come here would be Mon-Wed mid day lines aren't to craz

Long story short--I understand the hype; I was doubtful  that I'd be satiated with only two tenders, but once I saw them...it was a game changer. The cashier told me "medium" spice level was equivalent to that of hot cheetos, and as someone who likes to enjoy my food rather than burn my tongue off, I opted for that level. Perfect heat level for me personally, and despite the line, my food was ready fairly quickly. Great experience overall, thanks Chicken and Farm Shop

The food here is definitely worthy of the hype!!! We got the fried chicken, cornbread, and two sides. EVERYTHING WAS SO GOOD! The chicken is really crisp and spiced and the honey butter goes so well with it. For the sides we got the pimento mac n cheese and mashed potatoes and they were so flavorful. I even really liked the cornbread and I'm usually not a fan of cornbread in general.  The food was amazing and we will definitely be back soon!!

Chicken & Farm Shop is such a solid place in the heart of West Loop! I was surprised that the restaurant was smaller than I expected, but the space was super cute and well-decorated (as expected with anything in Soho House).  I came for dinner with a friend and we got the chicken and waffles, dirty burger, and coleslaw, as well as two kinds of beer on the menu. The chicken and waffles were definitely the best I've ever had, especially with the house hot sauce. The dirty burger reminded me of In-N-Out, but in the best way possible. The burger was a bit small but reflected the price fairly. The coleslaw was a surprise favorite of the night for me. It was light and refreshing, and definitely enough for two or more to share.  I'd recommend coming here for lunch or brunch rather than dinner. When I came for dinner, there were more people there for drinks than food, and the portions also felt a bit lacking. Whether you come for brunch or dinner though, the ambiance and service will be top-notch and you're sure to have a pleasant experience!

Would recommend.  My Dirty Chicken Sandwich had fried chicken and a burger, along with tomato, lettuce, pickles, cheese all under one bun. Super disappointed in the service. No one was seating and we waited a few minutes. so I went to ask the only worker I saw if there was a host or should we seat ourselves and he rather rudely stated to wait to be seated. Once seated he poured water and took our drink order, then brought my husband his beer. Then we waited and watched 3 other tables get seated and order food before we were ever approached again. I had to stare down a different server to get waited on. Then we watched as everyone else got their food. When ours finally came, half the food was cold (butter doesn't melt on a waffle?) and half was too hot to eat. Other servers eventually started working and it got a little better regarding asking if we wanted more drinks or food, that is until we were completely done and then waited and waited for someone to bring us a bill. I had a bad experience here, and I will not be giving it another shot. The food was overpriced and not executed well, one of our food items was legitimately bad (as in bad / sour dairy), and the service was poor.  My wife and I came here and shared the chicken dinner special, which is $40 for a rotisserie chicken and 2 sides. The chicken was OK at best. The white meat was dry, and the seasoning on the chicken was nothing special at all. I expected a very flavorful chicken from a place named after it’s chicken.  One of the sides we selected was mac and cheese. Not only was the texture lumpy and gritty, some of the dairy was bad. It was legitimately sour, you could smell it. When we told our server about this, she told us she didn’t know how to take it off our bill because it was part of the dinner special so we should just reorder something else. After some back and forth she finally went to find someone else who knew how to deal with it.  The other side we had was the Brussels sprouts, which were sufficient. They were the lone bright spot of my visit. Even apart from the mac and cheese debacle, the service was generally inattentive even though the restaurant is very small and it’s easy to keep tabs on the entire place.

I can’t speak for the quality of the food because I never got a chance to order. I noticed Chicken & Farm on the food delivery site Doordash and it did look very appetizing.  BUT with a couple of exceptions most of the prices on Doordash are between $2-$5 higher per item than Chicken & Farm Shop.  So I call Chicken & Farm in hopes this was an error; first person was so confident she could help me, she couldn’t so she transferred me to a restaurant manager. The manager tries to tell me it was for delivery! Huh?! Chicago & Farm upcharges the takeout menu to cover delivery from third source who also charges, delivery, service fee, tax and gratuity?!  Nope not going for that. It makes no sense. I tell him this and he quickly say he’ll get a manager. I thought he was the manager. He puts me on hold, and I’m guessing since no one could answer the question they left me on hold and would periodically pick up, then place me back me on hold. After 11 minutes, I finally hung up. The space is also super cool and feels sort of exclusive being partially hidden within The Allis/Soho House. I have eaten at Chicken and Farm Shop 3 times in the past 1.5 months.  The food is always great- I've had the Chicken and Waffles twice and it can't be beat.  Even friends from the South have had good comments.  The reason for the 2-star rating is the service.  First, not everyone's food comes out at the same time. During my second visit, I had to ask if my entree was coming out since other people at my 4-person table had received their food and almost 5 minutes had passed. Second, we've had to ask our waiter for a second round of drinks at EACH visit. You would think they would be more on top of this since it means more money!  Finally, I or someone else has had to ask for our bill at each visit.  It was clear that we were done eating (plates had been cleared) and drinks were finished.  We were just sitting there and kept looking when a couple or group would come up to see if seating was available, and the waiter would just look around and shake his head.  All in all, good food and drinks, but if you are short on time and need to get somewhere quick, this isn't your place unless you are OK being aggressive with the wait staff.

This restaurant is in Soho House, and it is on the second floor. When you walk in the front of Soho House, there will be a lot of people who are ignoring you , go to your right, pass the bar  and go all the way to the stairs.  Walk up the stairs, down the hallway and you will arrive in the chicken and farm shop.  The rustic decor is in sharp contrast to the rest of Soho house, and I was told by our waiter that the space used to be a leather shop.  The menu is chicken, chicken, and more chicken, soup and salad or burgers.  For dessert your have your choice of apple pie, brownie, or banana pudding.  The drinks menu is more extensive and they offer soft drinks, cocktails, beer and wine or milkshakes.  We took the advice of both our waiter and Yelp reviewers and ordered the chicken and waffles and the fried chicken sandwich.  We've never had the chicken and waffles before, and boy are we glad that we did. Really, really enjoyed it. The fried chicken sandwich was huge and we actually ended up splitting the chicken and waffles and taking the chicken sandwich home. Our side was the coleslaw, which was a large bowl and was shared by two people.  If you order one of the lunch specials, you have a choice of a dirty burger or a dirty Cop Out Burger, the fried chicken sandwich, or a quarter chicken. These are each served with your choice of one side and a soft drink or iced tea.  For dessert we had apple pie which was very authentic American, great tasting and reminded me of the kind your mom used to make.  The restaurant is very casual and I would recommend making a reservation for the weekends.  They definitely know how to do chicken, and I look forward to returning to trying one of their burgers.
Expertly cooked whole chicken. Fast service.

The place is amazing. The environment is very cozy too. The waiters are very friendly and funny, and the food is delicious. Everything is Chicken, but it is well cooked. The nuggets and the burger where my favorite.

We are talking about a Sunday in March. Understaffed, plus this place was out of half their menu items. The menu was way too sparse with the explanations. As in, There aren't any. Would you expect fried brussel sprouts to come tossed in a soy based sauce? I don't want to spend an extra 5 minutes asking questions about everything on menu,  especially when you're clearly understaffed. I already had to wait too long for the waiter in the first place. And all the tables were too small for any party greater than two. If you're going to offer me everything on the menu a lá carte at a premium price, meaning everything comes on its own separate plate, the least you could do is ensure I don't have to play a space efficiency game when my food comes.

First time here. Hopefully this place is having very bad day. Severely understaffed (even before half the tables filled up) and out of multiple things we wanted. The food we were able to order was perfectly fine. Not sure it justifies the prices though
Chicken sandwich was so. good. Quick lunch time spot on a weekday with plenty of seating. A bit difficult to find since it's in the hotel, but there is plenty of signage.
Best barbeque chicken sandwhich I've ever had along with a delicious milkshake, great interior design, and very friendly staff!
Lunch specials were top notch. Very little crowd to compete against, but service was attentive and food was exceptional.

make sure you get a piece of the high quality chicken 🐓 🐥 🐔 in the same bite as the high quality waffle doused in the high quality syrup. chicken and waffles are 15$. its good tho bro park on lake street or fulton market and take your lady to get layed up with dankest chicken and waffles

Loved the food - had the chicken and waffles which were spectacular.  Flavors excelled. Service was lightening fast. Only drawback was the restaurant was extremely noisy and loud.   Felt more like a college bar than a restaurant.  But the food made up for it.   Give it a try.  You won't be sorry.

One of those places I don't 100% get but I think I like that. Sitting upstairs is very cosy. Your definitely in the company of chicken lovers. The menu is limited and the room is a little dark. Great experience.  Chicken sandwich is the bomb.
Effing Grrrrrrrrrreat!!!
Fun place and great food
Tried the chicken and waffles, chicken sandwich, and brussel sprouts, all of which were delicious.
I loved it here. Great food.

Great place the chicken and waffles are absolutely addictive.  Despite the name don't think that menu is limited to chicken.  The setup is different from any other restaurant I've visited, you actually have to enter through the restaurant on the ground level and walk up the shared, staircase to get to Chicken/Farm.  The atmosphere is very inviting, urban upscale located in Chicago's West loop area.  Street parking can be a difficult to find,  other than that service is fast, friendly staff and with great entrees and side dishes this place comes highly recommended.
Bomb chicken nuggets and biscuits
Amazing food and super friendly staff! Will definitely come back!
Get the chicken and waffles
They have one of the best milk shakes I've ever had in my life and they're chicken is amazing.
Best chicken sandwich I've ever had. Balanced, not too greasy, and generous portions.
Great food, great fast service, great atmosphere...we will return when visiting Chicago again!

Overall, I really enjoyed this restaurant! It was great service all around. Our server was outstanding. I didn’t exactly know what type of alcoholic beverage I wanted so I told our server what I liked and he brought back the perfect drink. He did great elaborating on the menu. I got the chicken and waffles and it was the best I’ve ever had. The brussel sprouts were so tasty! My husband got a chicken sandwich that he really liked. The atmosphere was super laid back and chill. I can’t wait to go back!

(Translated by Google) This roast chicken is really the best I have ever eaten! There are also muffin chicken chops that are super delicious and super special. Be sure to try them.  (Original) 這家的烤雞真的是我吃過最好吃的了！還有鬆餅雞排也是超好吃，超特別，一定要來試試。

You need more Stars! This is my favorite restaurant of the year! Omg the food is great I mean Everything is SUPER delicious!!!!The servers are helpful, friendly and knowledgeable. We ate good and really had the best time! Go go go! I love this place!!!!Yes
Amazing location.  The chicken sandwich is a winner.  Thank you

Quite a small place, but they deliver on the chicken. The chicken is a pretty big size and if you get the sandwich it’s difficult to eat, but delicious. Nice flavor on the chicken and it’s tender and moist. The chicken and waffles is good too. The waffles are light and fluffy as they should be. Their hot sauce is quite spicy so maybe not too generous with the sauce. The service was really friendly as well.
Food was awesome! Waiter gave us half off our entire bill to download the app!
Awesome
The best chicken and waffles in the city. Don't order the Mac and cheese, pretty gross. However, service, drinks, and the chicken on point!

Wait staff is friendly and attentive. This is a nice place to have drinks and a quiet enough atmosphere to enjoy conversation with a friend. But the food was very underwhelming. I was expecting better given the great reviews. Had the chicken nuggets as an app, the breading was unique but a bit dry. Had the chicken quarter (dark meat) which some bites were incredibly juicy and some were incredibly dry. Collards were excellent. Mac and cheese, chili was rather bland and tasteless.
Chicken sandwich and Mac n cheese here we're very good. Come with a group as they offer jug sized table drinks for sharing.
Best chicken and waffles I've ever had. Will certainly be back.
Great place to be
(Translated by Google) Very nice and charming place, unfortunately badly managed by the table staff  (Original) Locale molto bello e suggestivo purtroppo mal gestito da personale al tavolo
Delicious fried chicken and the most decadent  brownie a la mode ever!
Best chicken in town. You've got to also try their coleslaw and coctail jars.

Sept 29, 2017 I went for a friend's celebration and ordered the nuggets, corn and banana pudding. The dessert was amazing! The nuggets are a bit over battered...meaning there was so much breading it took away from the chicken, made it seem a little chewy. I wouldn't recommend those, but tried a friend's chicken dinner and it was amazing. The cornbread was also tasty. Be mindful, though, greens and beans are made/seasoned with pork so if that's an issue don't order them. Corn comes with cilantro - so if you don't like cilantro, like me, order it without cilantro.   The millions of peaches was a strong summery kind of drink but not sweet as expected, but comes in a larger glass than the other mixed drink options made with dark liquor. Great ambiance for a Friday after work--hardly no one there until after 6:30pm. Earlier this year.... I ordered the fried chicken sandwich plain with white cheddar cheese along with fries (lunch special comes with a side and soda...otherwise everything is a la carte). The fries weren't good, so I was glad when I decided to switch to corn -GRILLED SND BUTTERED TO PERFECTION!  The bun for the sandwich was super moist making the sandwich extra delicious.  Finally we ordered the warm brownie with ice cream- a wise choice !! This is upstairs from the exclusive SOHO HOUSE CHICAGO, but it is open to the public thankfully.
Chicken & Waffles!!!!
Good stuff
Cozy place in the West loop. Dirty Burger was excellent. Our server Fernando was polite and attentive.
Great fried chicken!
Legit Chicken Sandwich.
Great juicy chicken.
Staff was very helpful, food and drinks were super fast, ordered chicken nuggets, mac and cheese, and apple pie <3 I will 100% be back again!

Love the atmosphere, the chicken and waffle is a great option, but must wait couple of minutes to eat that fried chicken. It would taste better if u use some of the hot sauce (contains habanero). I recommend the chicken and waffle. I feel i wanna go back to try the fried chicken sandwich, but won't. Don't think i would go back to the place because of a personal issue regarding my payment last time.
I like the service, not rushed. Very friendly and knowledgeable staff. The burgers are very good and I like the fried chicken and waffle too. Maple butter was excellent!
The rotisserie chicken is amazing.

Southern-inspired staples in a candle-lit industrial building, located just off of Randolph in the West Loop. The chicken and waffles with its buttermilk and vanilla sweetness or the bbq fried chicken sandwich that has a slaw to complement its tanginess are top items on the menu.

Absolutely positively amazing! Was told that the fried chicken sandwich was heaven on Earth and I'll admit I was highly skeptical. When the sandwich came out looking like a tower of golden fried greatness, I was immediately in visual awe at how absolutely delectable it looked. I will admit, I was a little intimidated by how large it was so I had to cut it in half in order to make it more manageable. For sides, I ordered the cornbread and Mac and cheese, both of which were just ok and at the end of it too much, since the sandwich itself was so much. The ambience of the location on a Friday night was dope too. All in all, would recommend this place to anyone.
Ambience & food was awesome
Their chicken seasoning is on point and so are their sides and drinks. I will definitely make it a point to return 😃

Note that this review is for the BBQ chicken sandwich I sampled at Taste of Randolph. The line was super long, the temp was soaring and the humidity was thick but the servers were cheery and upbeat!  There are few fried chicken sandwiches I've ever tried that were this juicy and yet perfectly flaky crispy on the outside. I personally believe that angels are in the kitchen of this place frying chicken for the hungry believers in line. YES, IT WAS THAT GOOD THAT I'M TYPING IN ALL CAPS!!  I'll be back in town soon to eat at the actual location and I'll enter tithe in hand.
Really great food, brilliant staff. The portions are quite large and filling so keep that in mind when ordering food.
Great service and the Chicken & Waffles is to die for.
Go for the lunch specials if not you'll be spending quite a bit on lunch for two
I’m in love with the chicken sandwich. We went when it wasn’t too crowded so we got to talk with the chef - who was extremely nice. You could tell he was passionate about the food he was cooking.
Fried chicken sandwich, slaw, and iced tea for $15 at lunch is delicious and a great deal.
Such a vibe! This place was so good! I had the chicken and waffles and it was some of the best I've ever had.
Wow Great food and perfect service, Michael at the bar had perfect timing
Delicious chicken sandwich!
Excellent food great soho atmosphere!
A interesting place in a neighborhood with plenty of chicken choices.  Sample this an the others.
Everything on the menu is excellent.

What a nice place! I had double dirty burger- people who prepare food are master kitchen chefs. Burger was great!!!! All staff who working here is very friendly and professional. This is great place to stop by and eat something delicious for nice price. Restaurant and staff is friendly for families with kids. For sure I will back with friends:)
Fun atmosphere
Why do they have to kill my pet chicken (Mr. Cock) killed rip pet chicken!
Try the chicken and waffles. Service is friendly and fast
Flavorfull place. Nice kitchen.
Chicken is good and they have one of the best chocolate brownies in the city.

Chicken & Farm Shop is a restaurant connected to Soho House.  There's really cute seating outside which is great when the weather is nice.  The only problem was that our waitress was tending to both the outside tables and the inside ones, so she'd disappear for long periods.  I had the chicken and waffles which was amazing.  Honestly, amazing.  My friend got the vegetarian sandwich and found herself still hungry and a bit underwhelmed.  I don't think the portion sizes are great given the prices and the proximity to a TON of other(better?) restaurants in West Loop, but I loved my meal and that deserved at least 4 stars.
Delicious delicious delicious chicken
I love the deep  dish apple pie and my son loves the chicken strips.
Great atmosphere and amazing chicken and waffles. The moment you eat the chicken your mouth is filled with flavors.

Delicious food! Never had a Waffle with Fried Chicken on it, but went for it.  Great service - very attentive waiter.  While not the meal I would normally opt for I could not resist after hearing how good it was.  I'd agree! I work in the hood and will be visiting again, may opt for a much lighter lunch.  Check it out.  Neat building with a bar, coffee bar, two different restaurants.
Outstanding
I get the chicken & waffles everytime I come here. You'll find no better iteration of this dish anywhere in this city, I promise you.

A low light place set to look like a bootleg era bar and club.  Food was great, staff was awesome! Our party did not reserved a table, and the staff made it happen, they were unsung heroes of night.  A great place to eat with a group and start the night in town.
Download the app, and go on Monday nights for half hour. I recommend the chicken and waffles. If they have the gravy get that also. Corn muffins are a great starter.
This chicken is so good it's not even fair.  Paired with their house made sauce it's unreal.
Awesome rosted chicken and burgers!

Great meal!! Their rotisserie chicken is flavorful - it is coated with paprika. Make sure you squeeze the lemon on top for a great flavor burst.  Sides were great. Really enjoyed their fries and their house-made aioli, biscuit/cornbread with honey butter and coleslaw. We had leftover coleslaw so I ordered another quarter of chicken to takehome. Fyi, the leftovers made really good tacos... the only negative is lighting. It is dark.. you will definitely need a flashlight to look at the menu.
Great for handcrafted cocktails and CHICKEN! I went with a group of friends and ordered a few items on the menu to share.  The biggest hit was the chicken and waffles, a must try.

Love the chicken sandwich. Don't indulge in fried food much, but this sandwich was worth it. Comes on a brioche bun with avocado, lettuce & aioli. Moist and flavorful. My friend had the burger and was equally pleased. Filling sandwich as it should be because they run $15 each and don't include any side. Love the decor. And the service was very friendly. Will definitely return.
good food
Cool and interesting food. Great service!

Okay listen I have had burgers all over the us. From LA to New York and everywhere in between, and I have NEVER had anything which could rival the dirty burger with bacon and fried egg. If you love burgers you cannot complete your burger tourism without a stop here. Just do it. Also my girlfriend says the chicken sandwich is "dope."
The dirty burgers are delicious!  Also the corn on the cob was amazing.  If you order a bottle of wine you can finish it downstairs which is a nice area to hang out at.
The best chicken and waffle in Chicago
Simply delicious! The fried chicken sandwich was hot and juicy with the perfect amount of batter.  I will be coming back to get another one!

Delicious chicken and waffles!  The batter was perfect, not too heavy.  The chicken was very juicy and the mild taste of the buttermilk just sings and dances in your mouth. This might sound strange (but it really isn't), a little of the Maple syrup on the chicken was a taste of heaven!  The waffle was light and fluffy - Delish!  We also ordered the "Dirty Bacon Burger", which we were told they mixed in some bone marrow; it was sure very tasty.
Good food, service could have been better. (We didn't get our drinks until after we had gotten our food)

Tucked upstairs in the hip Soho House Hotel is a chicken lovers delight.  Don't expect gourmet dishes, this is comfort food in a rustic (but very well executed) environment.  The only downside of note is the tiny pours of wine which boarder on the ridiculous.
Amazing chicken, great service, unbelievable pie. All around outstanding.
Some of the best southern cooking in Chicago. The chicken is perfect. Plenty of great things on the menu, but chicken is a must. Also, the cocktails are great.
Possibly the best seasoned, most perfectly cooked chicken I've had, on repeated visits. Lovely sides, lovely cocktails. Instant favorite.

The restaurant is inside Soho House and has a rustic decor and not many tables.  We arrived around 7pm and there was no wait.  The menu is very simple, you order a size of a chicken of which we ordered a full chicken for two people with about 1/3 to take home for leftovers.  You also order a bunch of sides that you can share.  I liked the concept and the menu concept of having chicken is actually pretty original I thought for Chicago.  The service was great and the atmosphere was nice with trendy rustic decor.  The only downside was that the table was pretty small for 4 people and with the amount of food you are ordering.
